<item>
            <title>[FLUME-1240] Add version info to Flume NG</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLUME-1240</link>
                <project id="12311321" key="FLUME">Flume</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A user should have a way to know which version of Flume is being used. This can be implemented by adding a &apos;version&apos; command to the flume-ng shell script. For example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;     flume-ng version&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;...would result in the git commit # that the Flume NG build is based on. This would help with tracking a user&apos;s problems with using Flume.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I imagine that the build process would need to create some kind of buildinfo file that can be referenced by the script... that&apos;s just one idea. I&apos;m interested in what others think.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hadoop has the same feature: &quot;hadoop version&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
